  "question": "1) Define the terms: (a) Element (b) Atom (c) Molecule",
  "answer": "Element – It is a substance which cannot be further divided into two or more simpler\nsubstances.\nAtom –The smallest unit of element which may or may not have an independent existence\nbut always takes part in a chemical reaction is called an atom.\nMolecule –The smallest unit of a matter which has an independent existence and possesses\ncomplete physical and chemical properties of the matter is called molecule."
