  "answer": "The molecules of a liquid in a vessel are not stationary but are always in state of random\nmotion in all possible direction. In doing so, the molecules of liquid strike against the walls\nof the containing vessel. Hence they exert some specific force on the walls of the containing\nvessel. This force exerted per unit area on the walls of containing vessel is the cause of\nliquid pressure."
