  "question": "9) Explain the heating of iron rod by conduction on the basis of kinetic model.",
  "answer": "When an iron rod is heated from one end, its atoms gain heat energy at that end. This\ngain in heat energy increases the kinetic energy of the atoms. So the atoms vibrate more\nvigorously about their mean positions. So they strik\nthe neighbouring atoms and transfer a part of kinetic energy to them. In this way more and\nmore atoms along the length of the rod gain kinetic energy and hence the temperature of\nthe rod rises. Thus the iron rod is heated by conduction without actual movement of the\natoms."
