  "topicId": "ch2-measurement",
  "type": "short_answer",
  "subtopic": "Exercise Study Questions",
  "question": "15) Calculate the volume of wood of mass 6000 kg when the density of wood is 0.8 g cm-3",
  "answer": "mass=6000kg density =0.8 g cm-3=0.8 x100 kgm-3=800 kgm-3\n Volume = mass / density = (6000 kg) / (800 kg m-3 )= 7.5 m3"
