  "type": "short_answer",
  "subtopic": "Exercise 3.3",
  "question": "9)Define Pascal’s law.",
  "answer": "Pascal’s Law It states that when pressure is applied to any part of an enclosed liquid, it is\ntransmitted equally in all directions with undiminished force and acts at right angles to the\nsurface of vessels."
